Derivative status with respect to Debian GNU/Linux
--------------------------------------------------
AIMS OS is a derivative work of Debian GNU/Linux. It is built by
assembling unmodified binary packages from the official Debian
archive, plus a small set of original metapackages and configuration
maintained in this repository.

AIMS OS is NOT endorsed by, affiliated with, or supported by the
Debian Project. Bugs in AIMS OS should be reported to the AIMS Senegal
IT team, not to the Debian bug tracking system, unless the bug is
confirmed to exist in an unmodified upstream Debian package.

Per the Debian Trademark Policy
(https://www.debian.org/trademark), the name "Debian" and the Debian
swirl logo are trademarks of Software in the Public Interest, Inc.
AIMS OS does not use the Debian name in its branding and does not
ship the Debian logo in any user-visible surface.


